<br />
<h3>5. FAQ on your data</h3>

<br />
<h5>5.1 Is there any way you can get this data "for yourself"?</h5>
<strong>No</strong>. All your data is stored encrypted. We do not have direct access to it.
Automated tools are used to recover your accounts and interactions between site elements by interacting with <code>accounts token</code>. Its current version is generated partly on the client side (i.e. your browser) and partly on our servers. We are unable to access the full version.
<br />
<br />
<h5>5.2 How do I request my data?</h5>
All you have to do is go to your account settings, then to the <code>Personal Information</code> section and click on <code>Request Personal Information</code>. You will then have to wait between a day and a week for our servers to collect your personal data from the databases.

